textAnnotations.description:
With four cloing the job and the waves
pusthing at the stern, the yowl was soon
dragged out but before it was turned
over Bueno Buck reached into the foot
of silvery
of water, tossed out a
string
lake trout and said - 3" Bill, he's better
man at catch 'em than Injun, Judge.
You look. Little one more as fifteen
inches. Maybe big one four feet,
huh?"
